BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ddc-trygfonden-fellowship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Digital Democracy Centre x TrygFonden Fellowship Program 
 2027
DESCRIPTION:The Digital Democracy Centre (DDC) at the University of Souther
 n Denmark\, with support from TrygFonden\, is calling for applications for
  its 2027 fellowship cohort. The program fosters collaboration between res
 earchers\, journalists\, and policymakers exploring the impact of digital 
 technology and AI on media\, politics\, and democracy. Fellows collaborate
  with a self-selected DDC mentor to generate new knowledge\, contribute to
  public debate\, develop networks\, and produce tangible outreach outputs 
 such as policy briefs\, educational packages\, and talks. THREE FELLOWSHIP
  TYPES: (1) academic fellows researching digital technologies and democrac
 y\; (2) journalist fellows covering digital technology and democracy\; (3)
  policy fellows contributing to the regulatory debate. Target group: resea
 rchers\, journalism graduates\, and policymakers in research/educational i
 nstitutions\, media organizations\, ministries\, NGOs\, etc. PRIORITIES: p
 rojects with clear relevance to Denmark or Danish society (including compa
 rative/international projects yielding insights relevant to a Danish conte
 xt)\; in 2027\, projects related to DDC's Hybrid Warfare Initiative (socie
 tal resilience to new forms of international conflict\, with a focus on di
 gital technologies and AI) are also prioritized. EXPECTATIONS: applicants 
 must secure confirmation of mentorship from their desired DDC mentor BEFOR
 E applying (applications without a confirmed mentor are automatically reje
 cted\; PhD students and research assistants are generally not eligible as 
 mentors\, and Sten Schaumburg-Muller is unavailable as a mentor for the 20
 27 call)\; applicants must also coordinate support from their current supe
 rvisors/managers. Fellows engage in DDC activities\, seminars/workshops\, 
 and public outreach\, and submit a short report within two months of finis
 hing. APPLICATION (in English): preliminary project title\, fellowship typ
 e\, brief project description (max 1000 chars)\, detailed description and 
 timeline (max 2400 chars\, including duration\, confirmed mentor\, and rem
 ote/in-office work plan)\, description of activities and collaboration wit
 h external practice partners (max 1000 chars)\, expected product/impact/ou
 tput (max 500 chars)\, a CV (max 5 pages)\, and an overview of the posts f
 or which financial support is sought. Submit the application form (PDF or 
 Word) plus CV as PDFs to ddc@sdu.dk with subject line 'DDC / TrygFonden Fe
 llowship application'. Deadline 1 September 2026\; decisions communicated 
 no later than 1 October 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Digital Democracy Centre (U
 niversity of Southern Denmark)\, with support from TrygFonden\nLocation: O
 dense\, Denmark (University of Southern Denmark). Flexible mix of in-offic
 e stays at the DDC in Odense and remote periods\; stays planned to the Dan
 ish working calendar.\nAward: Either a salary subsidy or a stipend to help
  with travel and/or housing\; specific benefits (financial support\, acces
 s to DDC research resources\, flexible working spaces\, speaker series\, n
 etworks) vary by agreement between the fellow\, DDC\, and partnering organ
 izations. Applicants describe the posts they seek support for (flights\, h
 ousing\, research costs\, salary compensation\, stipend\, etc.).\nDuration
 : Flexible\; typically 2-6 months (minimum two months\, can include shorte
 r DDC stays and remote periods)\, longer in exceptional cases. Fellowships
  start anywhere in 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.sdu.dk/en/forskning/forsknin
 gsenheder/samf/digitaldemocracycentre/news+folder/ddcxtrygfonden-fellowshi
 p-call-2027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.sdu.dk/en/forskning/forskningsenheder/samf/digitaldemocracy
 centre/news+folder/ddcxtrygfonden-fellowship-call-2027?utm_source=artifici
 alnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Odense\, Denmark (University of Southern Denmark). Flexible mix of
  in-office stays at the DDC in Odense and remote periods\; stays planned t
 o the Danish working calendar.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cais-research-sabbaticals-2027-28@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260723
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260724
SUMMARY:Deadline: CAIS Research Sabbaticals (Fellowships) 2027-28
DESCRIPTION:Residential research sabbaticals at CAIS\, explicitly open to e
 xcellent scholars AND practitioners across all career stages and disciplin
 es (not academia-only). Funds individual projects on the societal impact o
 f digital transformation\, including pure research and applied projects th
 at develop new theories\, methods or perspectives for practice. Project mu
 st be self-contained with specific milestones and produce an independent o
 utput suitable for short-timeframe publication: peer-reviewed paper or con
 ference contribution\, book chapter\, policy paper\, or prototype. Fellows
  join a vibrant interdisciplinary research community with regular joint ac
 tivities (breakfast Tuesdays\, colloquium and dinner Wednesdays\, occasion
 al workshops Thursdays) and an international network of alumni\, working g
 roups and affiliates. In Germany\, full and compensatory grants are not su
 bject to social security contributions and are usually tax-exempt\; fellow
 s resident abroad should verify their own tax position. Note: CAIS is curr
 ently reviewing the application format and selection process for the next 
 call\, so details may change. Next call publishes at the beginning of June
  2026\; deadline 23 July 2026 for fellowships in the period October 2027 t
 o March 2028. Contact: Dr. Esther Laufer\, esther.laufer@cais-research.de.
 \n\nOrganisation: Center for Advanced Internet Studies (CAIS)\, Bochum\, G
 ermany\nLocation: Bochum\, Germany (residential at CAIS\; rent-free\, full
 y furnished apartment provided plus private office)\nAward: Sabbatical lea
 ve on full salary: additional €600/month grant. No regular income: €2\
 ,000/month grant. Regular income below €1\,400/month: top-up to the full
  grant. Alternative: reimbursement of salary or substitute costs within re
 asonable limits. €100/month extra per child under 18 for fellows on a fu
 ll or compensatory grant. CAIS also covers one return trip to Bochum (or a
  daily commute if local)\, provides a rent-free fully furnished apartment 
 and a private office. Fellows can request financial support for research e
 xpenses\, invite a Visiting Fellow for up to 3 weeks of collaboration\, an
 d invite up to three European experts for half-day workshops (CAIS covers 
 travel\, accommodation and a daily allowance of up to €24).\nDuration: 3
  or 6 months. 6-month fellowships usually start in October or April\; 3-mo
 nth fellowships start in October\, January\, April or July. Exceptions pos
 sible by arrangement.\n\nMore: https://www.cais-research.de/en/cais-colleg
 e/fellowships/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.cais-research.de/en/cais-college/fellowships/?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Bochum\, Germany (residential at CAIS\; rent-free\, fully furnishe
 d apartment provided plus private office)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:msca-postdoctoral-fellowships-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260909
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260910
SUMMARY:Deadline: Marie Skłodowska-Curie Postdoctoral Fellowships 2026 (MS
 CA-PF)
DESCRIPTION:MSCA Postdoctoral Fellowships support researchers holding a PhD
  who wish to carry out research abroad\, acquire new skills\, develop thei
 r careers and have international mobility. Open to excellent researchers o
 f any nationality. The 2026 call opened 9 April 2026 and closes 9 Septembe
 r 2026 at 17:00 CEST\; notification of call results expected February 2027
 \; grant agreement signature April 2027. Two strands: European Postdoctora
 l Fellowships (12 to 24 months in Europe) and Global Postdoctoral Fellowsh
 ips (12 to 24 months outside Europe + 12-month return phase in Europe). Th
 e project must take place in a country different from where the researcher
  has worked or studied. Approximately 1\,600 projects funded. Apply via th
 e EU Funding & Tenders Opportunities Portal\; submission is by the fellow 
 plus host institution. Eligibility: researcher must have a PhD at the call
  deadline (or have submitted thesis with all requirements met)\, maximum 8
  years full-time-equivalent research experience post-PhD\, must comply wit
 h the mobility rule (no more than 12 months in the host country in the 36 
 months before the deadline).\n\nOrganisation: European Commission (Marie S
 kłodowska-Curie Actions\, under Horizon Europe\; managed by the European 
 Research Executive Agency\, REA)\nLocation: Europe (host institution in an
  EU Member State or Horizon Europe Associated Country\; also possible: Glo
 bal Postdoctoral Fellowships hosted in non-associated third countries with
  a return phase in Europe)\nAward: Standard MSCA unit costs covering resea
 rcher allowance (living\, mobility\, family)\, research/training/networkin
 g costs and management/indirect costs (annual values published in the call
 's Work Programme\; typically a fully-funded postdoc package of roughly 
 €5\,000 to €8\,000+ per researcher per month equivalent depending on h
 ost country correction coefficient)\nDuration: 12 to 24 months (European P
 ostdoctoral Fellowships)\; Global Postdoctoral Fellowships are 24 to 36 mo
 nths including a 12-month return phase in Europe\n\nMore: https://marie-sk
 lodowska-curie-actions.ec.europa.eu/funding/msca-postdoctoral-fellowships-
 2026?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://marie-sklodowska-curie-actions.ec.europa.eu/funding/msca-postdo
 ctoral-fellowships-2026?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=r
 eferral
LOCATION:Europe (host institution in an EU Member State or Horizon Europe A
 ssociated Country\; also possible: Global Postdoctoral Fellowships hosted 
 in non-associated third countries with a return phase in Europe)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:einstein-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260515
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260516
SUMMARY:Deadline: Einstein Fellowship 2026 (Einstein Forum + Wittenstein Fo
 undation)
DESCRIPTION:Six-month residential fellowship for outstanding young thinkers
  (under 35) who\, in addition to producing strong work in their primary fi
 eld\, want to pursue a project in a different discipline\, following Einst
 ein's own cross-disciplinary example. Eligibility: candidates must be unde
 r 35 and hold a university degree in the humanities\, social sciences\, or
  natural sciences. Whether the applicant holds\, or is working toward\, a 
 PhD is not relevant. Crucially\, the proposed project must be significantl
 y different in content (and preferably in field and form) from the applica
 nt's previous work\; this is NOT a dissertation-research grant and is NOT 
 for completing an academic study already underway. The project need not be
  finished during the fellowship\, but can be the start of a longer one. Se
 lection criteria: quality\, originality\, and feasibility of the proposed 
 project\, plus the superior intellectual development of the applicant. App
 lication materials: CV\, a 2-page project proposal\, and two letters of re
 commendation\, all submitted via the online form. All documents must be re
 ceived by 15 May 2026. Funded by the Wittenstein Foundation (previously fu
 nded by the ZEIT Foundation Ebelin and Gerd Bucerius 2007 to 2009\, then t
 he Daimler and Benz Foundation 2010 to 2022).\n\nOrganisation: Einstein Fo
 rum (with the Wittenstein Foundation)\nLocation: Caputh\, Brandenburg\, Ge
 rmany (garden cottage at Einstein's summerhouse\, near Potsdam and Berlin)
 \nAward: EUR 10\,000 stipend + living accommodations for six months at Ein
 stein's summerhouse + travel expense reimbursement\nDuration: 6 months in 
 residence at the Einstein summerhouse cottage. End-of-term: present the pr
 oject in a public talk at the Einstein Forum and at the Wittenstein Founda
 tion.\n\nMore: https://www.einsteinforum.de/en/about/fellowship/?utm_sourc
 e=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.einsteinforum.de/en/about/fellowship/?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Caputh\, Brandenburg\, Germany (garden cottage at Einstein's summe
 rhouse\, near Potsdam and Berlin)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:journalismfund-europe-cross-border-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260730
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260731
SUMMARY:Deadline: Journalismfund Europe: European Cross-Border Grants
DESCRIPTION:Supports independent investigative journalism across Europe\, w
 ell-suited to surveillance\, AI\, platform governance and data-driven inve
 stigations. Cross-border team requirement: at least two professional journ
 alists (freelance or staff) from at least two different countries\; at lea
 st 80% of the budget must go to journalists/media from EU member states. T
 he next round closes 30 July 2026 at 1 pm CET.\n\nOrganisation: Journalism
 fund Europe\nLocation: Europe (cross-border projects)\nAward: Variable per
 -team grants (typically a few thousand to ~EUR 20\,000+). The July 2026 ro
 und has a total budget of around EUR 280\,000.\nDuration: Per project\n\nM
 ore: https://www.journalismfund.eu/grants?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.journalismfund.eu/grants?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Europe (cross-border projects)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fias-fellowship-programme-2027-2028@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260625
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260626
SUMMARY:Deadline: French Institutes for Advanced Study (FIAS) Fellowship Pr
 ogramme 2027-2028
DESCRIPTION:FIAS Fellowship Programme offers 10-month fellowships at seven 
 Institutes for Advanced Study in France\, welcoming high-level internation
 al scholars and scientists to develop innovative research projects. 29 POS
 ITIONS for 2027/2028: Aix-Marseille (7)\; Cergy (3)\; Loire Valley/Orleans
 -Tours (2)\; Lyon (3)\; Montpellier (2)\; Nantes (4)\; Paris (8). DISCIPLI
 NES: all Social Sciences and Humanities (SSH) plus all other research fiel
 ds interfacing with the SSH. ELIGIBILITY: outstanding researchers at all c
 areer levels\, from postdoctoral to senior scientists. Minimum: PhD plus 2
  years of research experience at the time of application. Researchers from
  all countries are eligible BUT must have spent no more than 12 months in 
 France during the three years prior to the application deadline. COMMON ST
 ANDARDS across all FIAS: living allowance of EUR 2\,200/month\; social sec
 urity coverage\; accommodation\; research and training budget\; travel exp
 enses covered. DEADLINE: 25 June 2026. APPLY via the FIAS-FP call for appl
 ications page.\n\nOrganisation: French Institutes for Advanced Study (FIAS
 ) network: Aix-Marseille\, Cergy\, Loire Valley (Orleans-Tours)\, Lyon\, M
 ontpellier\, Nantes\, Paris\nLocation: Seven Institutes for Advanced Study
  across France (Aix-Marseille\, Cergy\, Loire Valley/Orleans-Tours\, Lyon\
 , Montpellier\, Nantes\, Paris)\nAward: EUR 2\,200/month living allowance\
 ; social security coverage\; accommodation\; research and training budget\
 ; travel expenses covered. No application fee.\nDuration: 10-month fellows
 hip during the 2027/2028 academic year\n\nMore: https://www.fias-fp.eu/fel
 lowships/call-applications-20272028?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.fias-fp.eu/fellowships/call-applications-20272028?utm_sourc
 e=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Seven Institutes for Advanced Study across France (Aix-Marseille\,
  Cergy\, Loire Valley/Orleans-Tours\, Lyon\, Montpellier\, Nantes\, Paris)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:horizon-europe-cl2-2026-heritage-ai-creative@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260923
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260924
SUMMARY:Deadline: Horizon Europe Cluster 2: Culture\, Creativity and Inclus
 ive Society (HORIZON-CL2-2026-01-HERITAGE) — incl. AI and Creative Conte
 nt topic
DESCRIPTION:Horizon Europe Cluster 2 funds research on culture\, creativity
 \, and inclusive society. The 2026 call (HORIZON-CL2-2026-01-HERITAGE\, la
 unched May 12\, 2026) covers 7 topics with an indicative budget of €85.5
  million. Topic HERITAGE-04 is explicitly titled 'Towards a fair and trans
 parent market for cultural and creative content in the era of generative A
 I\,' covering: impacts of generative AI on creative industries employment\
 ; upskilling needs for creative workers\; policy and regulatory frameworks
 \; fair remuneration and transparency. Highly relevant for research into A
 I and cultural/creative industries\, artists' rights in the AI era\, and s
 ociotechnical studies of AI and culture. ELIGIBILITY: consortium-based app
 lications (minimum 3 organisations from 3 different EU/associated countrie
 s are typical for Horizon RIA grants\; check call conditions on the Fundin
 g & Tenders portal for specific requirements). Deadline: 23 September 2026
 . Apply via the EU Funding & Tenders portal (ec.europa.eu/info/funding-ten
 ders).\n\nOrganisation: European Research Executive Agency (REA) / Europea
 n Commission\, Horizon Europe\nLocation: European Union and associated cou
 ntries. Consortium-based\; typically requires partners from multiple EU/Ho
 rizon member states.\nAward: Indicative total budget €85.5 million acros
 s 7 topics (2026 call). Individual project amounts vary by topic. Up to 10
 0% funding rate for non-profit research organizations. No application fee.
 \nDuration: Typically 3-4 years\; varies by topic.\n\nMore: https://rea.ec
 .europa.eu/funding-and-grants/horizon-europe-cluster-2-culture-creativity-
 and-inclusive-society/european-cultural-heritage-and-cultural-and-creative
 -industries_en?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://rea.ec.europa.eu/funding-and-grants/horizon-europe-cluster-2-cu
 lture-creativity-and-inclusive-society/european-cultural-heritage-and-cult
 ural-and-creative-industries_en?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
LOCATION:European Union and associated countries. Consortium-based\; typica
 lly requires partners from multiple EU/Horizon member states.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:european-commission-born-digital-heritage-2026@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260716
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260717
SUMMARY:Deadline: European Commission: Safeguarding Europe's Born-Digital H
 eritage (PPPA-2026-BORN-DIGITAL)
DESCRIPTION:The European Commission is offering a single grant of up to €
 1\,985\,000 (85% co-financing) for a project focused on safeguarding born-
 digital cultural heritage across EU member states. Scope includes: assessi
 ng the preservation state of born-digital art\, web archives\, video games
 \, and digital content created outside cultural institutions\; mapping EU 
 and national legal frameworks\; identifying non-legislative barriers (tech
 nical\, financial\, organisational\, cultural)\; and providing guidance on
  creating preservation copies of licensed or legally accessible materials.
  This is a scoping and advocacy project\, not a digitisation grant. ELIGIB
 ILITY: the application must be led by a consortium of at least 5 independe
 nt entities from 5 different EU countries\, which rules out solo applicant
 s and single-country organisations. Grant reference: PPPA-2026-BORN-DIGITA
 L. Deadline: 16 July 2026. Verify the current deadline at ec.europa.eu bef
 ore applying (one secondary source listed 1 June 2026\; the primary call-f
 iche PDF and the Cyprus government funding portal both confirm 16 July 202
 6).\n\nOrganisation: European Commission (Pilot Projects and Preparatory A
 ctions\, Culture strand)\nLocation: European Union. Consortium of at least
  5 independent entities from 5 different EU member states required.\nAward
 : Up to €1\,985\,000\, covering up to 85% of eligible project costs (15%
  co-financing required). No application fee.\nDuration: Project duration t
 o be defined in the proposal\; covers a scoping and mapping phase across E
 U member states.\n\nMore: https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opport
 unities/docs/2021-2027/pppa/wp-call/2026/call-fiche_pppa-2026-born-digital
 _en.pdf?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/
 pppa/wp-call/2026/call-fiche_pppa-2026-born-digital_en.pdf?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:European Union. Consortium of at least 5 independent entities from
  5 different EU member states required.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:royal-conservatoire-antwerp-research-proposals-2027@artificialnouveau.g
 ithub.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260921
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260922
SUMMARY:Deadline: Royal Conservatoire Antwerp: Call for Artistic Research P
 roposals (2027 start)
DESCRIPTION:The Royal Conservatoire Antwerp (AP University of the Arts) inv
 ites applications for artistic research projects starting 20 September 202
 7\, in three types: start projects\, one-year projects\, and two-year rese
 arch projects. Applications are embedded in one or more of the Conservatoi
 re's four research groups\, supervised by a supervisor\, and must align wi
 th the Conservatoire's mission and vision. FOCAL POINTS across disciplines
 : research into improvisation and intuitive creation and performance pract
 ices\; new dramaturgical and scenographic approaches in cross-over project
 s\; methodologies for interdisciplinary creation processes\; sustainable r
 elationships between artists and urban communities\; the possibilities and
  limitations of inclusion in education and/or on stage\; and well-being an
 d resilience in music and performing arts. FUNDING (salaried research posi
 tion): start projects\, 20% employment for 12 months plus EUR 1\,000 opera
 ting resources\; one-year projects\, 55% employment for 12 months plus EUR
  1\,000\; two-year projects\, 55% employment for 24 months plus EUR 2\,000
 . PRECONDITIONS: the applicant holds a relevant master's degree and conduc
 ts research situated in or arising from their own artistic practice with t
 he capacity for discursivity\; the proposal must align with the Conservato
 ire's mission/vision\; the applicant must be able to enter contractual emp
 loyment with the Royal Conservatoire Antwerp/AP University of the Arts for
  the duration of the project (international applicants must hold a valid B
 elgian work permit)\; proposals may be submitted only in Dutch or English.
  PROCEDURE (two steps): STEP 1\, submit an expression of interest by 21 Se
 ptember 2026\, 12:00 noon (applicants informed by the week of 5 October wh
 ether they may develop a full proposal with a research group)\; STEP 2\, s
 ubmit the full project dossier by 1 December 2026\, 12:00 noon. Evaluation
  by an independent reading committee aims to conclude in March 2027. Conta
 ct: Kevin Voets\, Head of Research\, kevin.voets@ap.be.\n\nOrganisation: R
 oyal Conservatoire Antwerp (AP University of the Arts)\nLocation: Antwerp\
 , Belgium. Salaried research position\; international applicants must hold
  a valid Belgian work permit.\nAward: Salaried research position (contract
 ual appointment). Start projects: 20% employment for 12 months + EUR 1\,00
 0 operating resources. One-year projects: 55% employment for 12 months + E
 UR 1\,000. Two-year projects: 55% employment for 24 months + EUR 2\,000. N
 o application fee.\nDuration: Projects start at the earliest 20 September 
 2027. Start and one-year projects run 12 months\; two-year projects run 24
  months.\n\nMore: https://www.ap-arts.be/en/submit-research-proposal-royal
 -conservatoire-antwerp?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
URL:https://www.ap-arts.be/en/submit-research-proposal-royal-conservatoire-
 antwerp?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Antwerp\, Belgium. Salaried research position\; international appl
 icants must hold a valid Belgian work permit.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:royal-academy-fine-arts-antwerp-research-proposals-2027@artificialnouve
 au.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T170129Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261103
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261104
SUMMARY:Deadline: Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp: Call for Two-Year Res
 earch Proposals (2027 start)
DESCRIPTION:The Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp (AP University of Applie
 d Sciences and Arts) invites applications for two-year artistic research p
 rojects starting 20 September 2027. Two-year research projects provide 55%
  employment for the research assignment over 24 months (as a contractual p
 roject staff member) plus EUR 2\,000 in operating funds (EUR 1\,000 per pr
 oject year). Proposals are developed in collaboration with the Academy's r
 esearch groups and must align with\, endorse\, and further develop the mis
 sion and vision of the Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp. PRECONDITIONS: 
 the proposal must be in line with the Academy's mission/vision\; the appli
 cant must be legally employable by the Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp/
 AP Hogeschool on a contractual basis\; and\, at the time of application\, 
 the applicant must hold a Master's degree in Visual Arts awarded by a Belg
 ian higher education institution (a non-Belgian degree is possible only if
  validated or recognised through the NARIC procedure\, with proof included
  or a declared willingness to undergo it). PROCEDURE (two steps): STEP 1\,
  apply via the Expression of Interest form sent to research_royalacademyan
 twerp@ap.be before 3 November 2026\, 12:00 noon (applicants informed no la
 ter than end November 2026 whether they may develop a full dossier)\; STEP
  2\, submit the full dossier via the two-year project application form bef
 ore 1 February 2027\, 12:00 noon. Evaluation by an independent reading com
 mittee aims to conclude in May 2027. Contact: research_royalacademyantwerp
 @ap.be.\n\nOrganisation: Royal Academy of Fine Arts Antwerp (AP University
  of Applied Sciences and Arts)\nLocation: Antwerp\, Belgium. Salaried rese
 arch position\; applicant must be legally employable in Belgium.\nAward: T
 wo-year research projects: 55% employment for the research assignment over
  24 months (contractual project staff member) plus EUR 2\,000 in operating
  funds (EUR 1\,000 per project year). No application fee.\nDuration: Two-y
 ear projects (24 months). Projects start at the earliest 20 September 2027
 .\n\nMore: https://www.ap-arts.be/en/submit-research-proposal-royal-academ
 y-fine-arts-antwerp?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refer
 ral
URL:https://www.ap-arts.be/en/submit-research-proposal-royal-academy-fine-a
 rts-antwerp?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Antwerp\, Belgium. Salaried research position\; applicant must be 
 legally employable in Belgium.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
